remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoderFrame` packages the pixel data and frame duration needed by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated*> to build an animated WebP file.
Each frame holds an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> and a `TimeSpan` that controls
how long the frame is displayed.

Convenience constructors accept an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKBitmap> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKImage> and automatically call `PeekPixels()` to obtain the
underlying pixmap. Both source objects must remain alive for the duration of
the encoding call.

This is a value type (struct) and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
using var frame1 = new SKBitmap(320, 240);
using var canvas1 = new SKCanvas(frame1);
canvas1.Clear(SKColors.CornflowerBlue);

using var frame2 = new SKBitmap(320, 240);
using var canvas2 = new SKCanvas(frame2);
canvas2.Clear(SKColors.Tomato);

var frames = new SKWebpEncoderFrame[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(frame1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(500)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(frame2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(500)),
};

var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, options);
File.WriteAllBytes("animated.webp", data.ToArray());
```
